Systemic arterial blood pressure and its relevance to optometric practice. The measurement of systemic blood pressure is a very significant detection test that can provide a great deal of information for the optometrist. The blood pressure readings can be critical in aiding the practitioner's evaluation of both the patient's visual health and related systemic condition and in indicating the possible need for referral. This paper presents a general survey of the benefits blood pressure measurements can provide in the optometric practice.